title: PML-N candidate Jam Kamal Khan wins PB-22 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate Jam Kamal Khan has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-22, Las Bela by securing 38,562 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) candidate Muhammad Hassam who bagged 18,373 votes.
Overall voters’ turnout remained 60.08 per cent.
